sub_title: Postdoctoral Researcher in medical physics at Erasmus MC
summary:
I'm currently working as a postdoctoral researcher and in parallel finalising my PhD in medical physics. Specifically I'm working on improving MR temperature measurements for hyperthermia treatments. I love collaborating with others to solve difficult problems and I enjoy jumping into the deep end. In the future I would like to continue making a positive tangible impact. Medical care and its accessibility, as well as effective communication of research are areas close to my heart. As a career path I'm hoping to apply my degree and my passion to the positive development of these areas. 

When I’m not on the job, I'm seldom sitting still. I love playing beach volleyball, exploring the outdoors and travelling. If there happens to be any time left in the day I relish being transported into different worlds by sci-fi books and spoil my surroundings with some home baked goods.
